# IAM directory boundary (`lib/auth/`)

## Authority

- **`lib/auth/`** owns the **IAM control plane**: Better Auth configuration, session/step-up guards, audit writers ([`audit.server.ts`](lib/auth/audit.server.ts)), org IAM audit CSV ([`org-audit.server.ts`](lib/auth/org-audit.server.ts), `org-audit-csv.shared.ts`, `org-audit-export-verify.server.ts`), and permission predicates ([`permission.server.ts`](lib/auth/permission.server.ts) — org role + global admin; no duplicate RBAC trees elsewhere).
- **`app/[locale]/…`** owns **routes and UI only** — do not introduce an `app/iam/*` URL tree for configuration authority.

## Import rules

- **Public server door:** `#lib/auth` → [`lib/auth/index.ts`](lib/auth/index.ts). Import `auth`, `requireRecentAuthStepUp`, and all guards from here.
- **Do not** deep-import `lib/auth/neon.server.ts` from `app/` or ERP features. **Exception:** low-level `lib` modules that load the Neon instance before the barrel (e.g. [`lib/session-cache.ts`](lib/session-cache.ts)) may use `#lib/auth/neon.server` only.
- **Shared helpers** (Edge/client-safe, no React, no `server-only`):
  - `#lib/auth/callback-path` — post-auth URL validation
  - `lib/auth/forwarded-path-headers.shared.ts` — proxy-safe header names (`proxy.ts` must not import `server-only` / `next/headers`)
  - `lib/auth/auth-status.shared.ts` — canonical interruption codes (`authStatus` query param)
  - `lib/auth/auth-interruption-url.shared.ts` — bookmarkable interruption URLs (requires `locale: AppLocale`)
  - `lib/auth/auth-client-error.shared.ts` — `normalizeAuthClientError`, `AUTH_CLIENT_ERROR_CODE` (client sign-in error normalization; not for server interruption URLs)
  - `lib/auth/auth-status-copy.ts` — UI copy resolver
- **Server-only helpers** (import via `#lib/auth` barrel):
  - `interruption-redirect.server.ts` + `intended-path.server.ts` — server redirect + path capture
  - `audit.server.ts` — `writeIamAuditEvent`, `writeIamAuditEventFromNextHeaders`
  - `iam-audit-telemetry.shared.ts` — `resolveIamAuditTelemetryEnabled` (Vercel log drain gate)

## Proxy and open-redirect validation

- **`proxy.ts`** stays **narrow**: cookie presence, redirects, matcher only — no business logic, no DB, no session body validation.
- **`callbackUrl`** must be validated for open redirects (same-origin relative paths only) via [`resolvePostAuthCallbackUrl`](lib/auth/callback-path.ts) before passing to client.

## ERP modules

- Do not embed IAM workflows inside `lib/features/<module>/` beyond calling guards or `#lib/auth` APIs.

## Audit action names

- `erp.<module>.<object>.<verb>` and `org.<object>.<verb>` for ERP/org events.
- `iam.session.*` for session lifecycle hooks.
- Full canonical list: **AGENTS.md §5 → IAM audit policy (ERP)**.

## Auth V2 canonical control plane

- V2 is the canonical Neon Auth control plane; see **`.cursor/rules/auth-v2-directory.mdc`** for the full boundary.
- Short version: `#lib/auth-v2` (server) / `#lib/auth-v2-client` (client); locale-first UI is organized via route groups under `app/[locale]/(auth)/**` and `app/[locale]/(iam)/**`; keep `lib/auth/` stable and avoid deep cross-imports between `lib/auth/*` and `lib/auth-v2/*`.

## Contract changes

- New filenames under `lib/auth/` or new IAM categories require updating **`AGENTS.md`** in the same change.
